SUMMARY:Finance - Week 4
DESCRIPTION:Topic: Bonds and Interest Rates\n\nObjectives:\n1. Calculate the price and yield of bonds using present value techniques.\n2. Explain why bond prices move inversely to interest rates.\n3. Assess the effects of maturity\, coupon rate\, and credit risk on bond valuation and yield.\n\nPre-Class Reading: Berk & DeMarzo (6th Ed.)\, Chapters 5 & 6\n\nAssignments Due This Week:\n- Homework 1: Wed Apr 8 @ 11:59pm\n- PulseLogic Case Study: Fri Apr 10 @ 11:59pm\n- Homework 2: Wed Apr 15 @ 11:59pm\n\nWeek 4 Page: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-4\nPulseLogic Assignment: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/9059518\nHomework 1: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/9006401\nHomework 2: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/9006397\nStudy.Net Materials: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/external_tools/79374\nAll Assignments: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments\nSyllabus: https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/assignments/syllabus
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bcourses.berkeley.edu/courses/1549853/pages/week-4
LOCATION:Chou Hall N370
